<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3465] Task metrics are not aggregated correctly in local mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3465</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In local mode, after onExecutorMetricsUpdate(), t.taskMetrics will be the same object with that in TaskContext (because there is no serialization for MetricsUpdate in local mode), then all the upcoming changes in metrics will be lost, because updateAggregateMetrics() only counts the difference in these two. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2099&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2099&lt;/a&gt;, cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sandyr&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sandyr&quot;&gt;sandyr&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;</description>
